DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,5,1);
$b = random(-6,6,1);
$c = random(-6,6,1);
$d = random(-6,6,1);
$e = random(2,5,1);
$f = random(-6,6,1);
$g = random(-6,6,1);
$h = random(-6,6,1);
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The expression \(($a b^{$b} c^{$c})^{$d} ($e b^{$f} a^{$g})^{$h}\) equals
\(na^rb^sc^t\) $BR where \(n\), the leading coefficient, is:
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $a**$d*$e**$h;
&ANS(strict_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and \(r\), the exponent of \(a\), is:
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =$g*$h;
&ANS(strict_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and \(s\), the exponent of \(b\), is:
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans =$b*$d+$f*$h;
&ANS(strict_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and finally \(t\), the exponent of \(c\), is:
\{ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
[NOTE:  Your answers cannot be algebraic expressions.]
$BR
EOT

$ans =$c*$d;
&ANS(strict_num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.

